            <!-- NEW DLC PLANET, visible in vanilla game skirmish-conquest panel -->
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>PLANET_DLC_01_ID</LocID>               <Text>UNSC 4298i/1 Typhon</Text>  </GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>PLANET_DLC_01_DESCRIPTION</LocID>      <Text>A habitable moon orbiting gas giant UNSC 4298i Atlas.\n\nThe UNSS poster states: Colonize Typhon, a green paradise with the famous Eye of Light anomaly! But colonists have a different story, "A day without St. Elmo's Fire trying to light your hair is a good day." \n\nAccording to officials, the Eye of Light's mysterious radiation is completely harmless even after long-term exposure.\n\nYeah, ... right. I bet the colonists will learn in a decade or two. And as usual, at that time, there will be no one to point a finger at. </Text>  </GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>MapEventPlayerActionType_TRIGGER_END_TURN</LocID>          <Text>Trigger end of turn of active player</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>

            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>MAPOBJ_DUNGEON_EXIT_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                    <Text>Back to the surface!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>MAPOBJ_DUNGEON_ENTRANCE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                <Text>Access to the underground layer.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_WILD_GEESE_BERET</LocID>                         <Text>Wild Geese Beret</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_WILD_GEESE_BERET_DESCRIPTION</LocID>             <Text>Your army's morale will never drop below zero!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_WILD_GEESE_BERET_LORE</LocID>                    <Text>Mercenaries? Yoh no! Not at all, bru, we are members of the Jo'burg Beer-Drinking Club. And we bring toys for the children from the Fossorian orphanage!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_SILVER_IODIDE_ROCKET</LocID>                     <Text>Silver Iodide Rocket</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_SILVER_IODIDE_ROCKET_DESCRIPTION</LocID>         <Text>Morale effects for both armies are negated!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>EQUIPMENT_SILVER_IODIDE_ROCKET_LORE</LocID>                <Text>Have you ever heard about "cloud seeding"? No? Never mind! The point is, if both armies are soaked to the bone, the morale will even out. Basically, it goes to hell, but for both, and that's what counts!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>HAS_NO_EFFECT_HERE</LocID>                                 <Text>has no effect here.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <!--  new neutral units  -->
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_RATLING</LocID>                               <Text>Ratling Troglodyte</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_RATLING_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                   <Text>Are we actually decelerating Ratling society development? If we leave them on their own, will they "rise"? But this experiment already happened! In the abandoned Fossorian bases, outposts, and mines, you can find Ratling castaways' tribes. Cult of the Shovel, Glue-sniffing zombies, Copper wire scavengers... I see a pattern here, but... I'll let you be the judge!  </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>

            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_ARMADILLO</LocID>                             <Text>Bullrock</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_ARMADILLO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                 <Text>You fire and miss. It's getting closer. Your hands turn sweaty. The gun feels heavier, clunkier than usual. Dial the max power! "We are not playing anymore!" Damn, it's way faster than it looks! Slow breath, aim... FLASH! The blinding beam scorches the air! Reek of ozone! Retina aches! Impact did not even slow it... A shaken "Sweet Mother" slips from your lips!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_ARMADILLO_PASSIVE_INFO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>    <Text>Automatically hardens its shell, becoming immune to ranged attacks until it attacks or counterattacks.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>DIALOG_COMBAT_END_MULTIPLAYER</LocID>                      <Text>The battle is over!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>DIALOG_COMBAT_END_MULTIPLAYER_TEXT</LocID>                 <Text>{1} is victorious!</Text></GameDBLocalizedString> <!-- Parameter {1} is player's name, similar to EXPLORATION_PLAYER_WON -->

